<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If a fire beetle approached you and began to attack you, would you simply sit there and let it? Or would you slay it promptly?<br>
<br>
Any opposition, no matter if it is a real threat or not, must be crushed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, I would simply sit there. I always keep both Barrier of Force and O'Keil's Levity on myself. The fire beetle would destroy itself, utterly fail to harm me, and I would waste not a whit of energy or time dealing with it. That is why Solusek Ro's reaction to the Four's plot reeks of Hatred...they should be to him what the fire beetle is to me. For some reason, they were not. Food for thought.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No, because to slay hundreds of thousands of beings wasn't his ultimate goal. It was simply a means to achieve his end - which was to curtail the influence of Tunare, and thus increase his own power. If his goal was to slay hundreds of thousands, he would be evil. But that wasn't his goal, his goal was to gain power - and just because you don't give a shit about what happens to hundreds of thousands of beings doesn't mean you fall on the evil end of the spectrum.<br>
<br>
It is intent that judges good or evil, not results. Innoruuk would have killed these elves simply out of malice. Solusek Ro killed them only to further his own ends. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
According to several reputed authorities, the total disregard for the lives of others in pursuit of one's own personal empowerment is called...<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:xx-large;">NEUTRAL EVIL!</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
It's just a label. But the fact is that no one is neutral...everyone picks a side. Just some don't recognize when they choose, nor what they chose. You chose a different sort of &quot;evil&quot; than I did...one that more closely monitors and restricts your actions to those it likes, lest it strip you of the power it granted you. What a sad way to live; deluded as to your purpose, serving a &quot;god&quot; who lies to you and enforces your dependance, and ultimately, intends to harvest the fruit of your labor for his own ends and cast you aside unless you turn out to be a total kissass.<br>
