<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>He would likely die...of laughter. No one man is a threat to the Prince of Hate. I suspect it would take dozens of powerful mortals to pose a threat to his true Avatar. In any case, as an immortal, he has no cause to fear destruction or death. His essence remains aware and viable at all times and will reform another Avatar when it suits him. Plots and schemes are encouraged among the worshippers of Innoruuk. It keeps the wits and skills sharp and the mind alert. Solusek Ro would of course discourage this among his faithful. An alert mind accustomed to diabolical plots might actually see what he's planning.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The Prince of Hate gathers his power off one thing: an emotion.  Vanquish the emotion, and you vanquish the god.  Your weak, pathetic excuse for a god's only source of power is derived from some petty emotion and those of weak kneed mortals.  Your fine diety nearly got overthrown by his own mortal daughter.  You wish to speak of traitors?  Your entire race is filled with them, althrough known have even approached the ability of treachery as Lanys did.  Solusek Ro influenced her more than the Prince of Hate ever did.  Indeed, if your god has such an alert mind, should this not be obvious to him? Yet I fail to hear of any retaliation from the Prince of Hate to the Burning Prine, as foolish as it may be.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I will allow you to keep your preconceived notions. Believe that followers of Innoruuk are weak. Believe that we are stupid. Believe that we cannot use our power properly nor handle ourselves adequately. Believe that there are no analogues to Solist or Jiva among Innoruuk's faithful. You will be much easier to deal with when the time comes if your power and mind are dulled by arrogance, overconfidence and pride. I need no crutch in battle...no rings, no staves, no armor. I have my mind and my magic. MY magic. Not Solusek Ro's nor Innoruuk's. If your perception is that you are outstripping anyone in terms of power, examine who holds your leash. I doubt, with your attitude towards study, that you are outstripping anyone at all in terms of knowledge. When the time comes, you will fall before the Hate of an adversary who is your lesser, for you underestimate us all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Go ahead, cling to your emotion.  Cling to it until it clouds your mind and destroys you.  Cling to it and know that the fall of the Tier'Dal soon comes.<br>
<br>
-Ikeya <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vdou>Vdou</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/27/03 10:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Take a good, hard look at Lanys. Yup, I think she fits all those criteria <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hey now, she happens to be one of my heroes. Her life is standard bedside reading for most Tier`Dal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They respect the powers of those greater than them and do not seek overwhelm those who are greater than them. Fire beetles are a fine example of how a follower of Solusek Ro should behave - respect the glory and power of the Burning Prince, for you can never compete with it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well said Ikeya.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Cling to it and know that the fall of the Tier'Dal soon comes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not before the Faydark burns with the mighty fires of Solusek himself!<br>
<br>
<br>
The true path to power through magic leads through Solusek's graces. The only reason anyone would have to follow any other diety is: <br>
<br>
a) They are just pawns of their heritage, or lackeys of the Church; in which case they are impotent and irrelevant in the large scheme of things. (Innoruuk and Tunareians for example)<br>
<br>
b) They are totally devoid of any moral sense and are so self absorbed that they refuse to aknowledge the non-existance/existance of any god as superior to themselves. (agnostics)<br>
<br>
c) Are wanna-be druids. (Followers of Karana)<br>
<br>
<br>
The worst of the worst fall into section 'b'. Agnosticism is the biggest cop-out ever, especially when gods and demi-gods play such active roles in our daily lives. <br>
<br>
Even followers of Karana have the sense to realize something is greater than themselves.<br>
<br>
All agnostics are spineless.<br>
<br>
